        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 18 at 1:22PM CDT by NWS Quad Cities IA IL</headline>
        <description>At 120 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a slow-moving thunderstorm
over Mechanicsville, moving east at 5 mph.

HAZARD...Minor flooding from heavy rainfall.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Slowing or redirecting of traffic due to ponding or flowing
water. Closure of waterfront access due to flooding.

Locations impacted include...
Mechanicsville, Stanwood, Mount Vernon, Lisbon, Buchanan, Cedar
Bluff, and Sutliff.

Rainfall amounts between 0.50 to 1.50 inches have fallen and
additional amounts between 0.50 to 1.50 inches of rain are possible.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
